# 🚀 CI/CD for a Containerized Application using Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS)


## 📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates an end-to-end DevOps workflow on Microsoft Azure.

A modern containerized web application is:

* Built using Docker
* Stored in Azure Container Registry (ACR)
* Automatically deployed to Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS)
* Managed through Azure DevOps CI/CD Pipelines
* Monitored using Azure Monitor and Prometheus

The objective is to showcase a complete cloud-native deployment pipeline following DevOps best practices.

---

# 🏗 Solution Architecture

![Architecture](screenshots/architecture.png)

## Workflow

```text
Developer
    │
    ▼
Azure Repos
    │
    ▼
Azure DevOps Pipeline
    │
    ├── Build Docker Image
    └── Push Image to ACR
            │
            ▼
Azure Container Registry
            │
            ▼
Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS)
            │
            ▼
Kubernetes Deployment
            │
            ▼
LoadBalancer Service
            │
            ▼
Users

Monitoring:
AKS → Prometheus → Azure Monitor
```

